Class MoneyHashMap<K,V extends Money>

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.util.AbstractMap<K,V>
      • java.util.HashMap<K,Money>
        • com.github.daytron.daytronmoney.collection.AbstractMoneyMap<K,Money>
          • com.github.daytron.daytronmoney.collection.MoneyHashMap<K,V>
  • Type Parameters:
    K - A generic data type that extends Object class
    V - A generic data type that extends Money class
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    MoneyCollection, Serializable, Cloneable, Map<K,Money>

    public class MoneyHashMap<K,V extends Money>
extends AbstractMoneyMap<K,Money>
    Custom data structure for handling Monies that extends the capabilities of a HashMap class. Implements custom methods from MoneyCollection interface and AbstractMoneyMap abstract class.
    Author:
    Ryan Gilera
